            Olympia is not a typical mid-sized city. As Washington's state capital, it faces security pressures that far exceed what a city of roughly 55,000 residents would normally encounter. The <strong>Washington State Legislative Building</strong> and surrounding Capitol Campus draw tens of thousands of visitors, lobbyists, staffers, and demonstrators each year -- creating a security environment more comparable to cities three or four times Olympia's size.
          </p>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-10">
