                Olympia has struggled with homeless encampments near Capitol Campus, along the waterfront, in Sylvester Park, and throughout the downtown core. These encampments have been associated with increased property crime, vandalism, and safety concerns for nearby businesses and government employees. The <strong>Capitol Lake / Estuary area</strong> and <strong>Marathon Park</strong> have been particular hotspots, prompting property managers and construction crews to invest in mobile surveillance.
              </p>
            </div>
